        <section>
        	<title>Syntax</title>

			<informalexample>
  				<programlisting>
<emphasis role="bold">unordered</emphasis> "{"
    ( &lt;Activity1&gt; ";" )+
"}"
     			</programlisting>
			</informalexample>
	
			<note>
			<para>
			Syntax to be defined. One possibility would be to find a symbol, other than
			';' to represent an ordered relationship between the activities. However this
			is easy to misread, and therefore misunderstand the description. We could
			use a similar structure as with <emphasis role="bold">parallel</emphasis>,
			with each unordered activity being in a separate path - this would enable
			groups of activities to be unordered - but then this would get confusing
			with parallel. The syntax above is another possibility, so use the same
			';' separate as sequence, but enclose in an 'unordered' region.
        	</para>
			</note>
			
